<div class="list-div auto-margin">

  <p class="left">Now, onto the matter at hand. Although
              there were many illegible pages due to the
              condition of the journal, our cryptologists
              concentrated on the leafs of testimony still
              preserved. With much diligence, we have
              unearthed a considerable amount of information
              for you.</p>
  <p class="left">After Bill Ryan's arrest at Earthman’s
              Store, both Captain Green and Charles Eastman
              waited for confirmation from Frank and Jesse
              that they had indeed absconded with the troves.
              When word failed to arrive, Green and Eastman
              followed the instructions left by the two
              brothers. They each secured the troves of
              their temples and relocated them to a final
              resting place. After doing so, they created
              a new key to the map. This new key, authored
              by Green and Eastman, as you know, was included
              in the destroyed pages of the journal. But, this
              is where luck smiles upon us! For Green and Eastman
              decided to leave the combined troves in rest
              at the Temple of the Sun! Which means the
              original key that Jesse contributed will still
              work! The key gives instructions to be
              followed from the Sam Watkins building to his
              home in Edgefield, and from there to the
              Temple of  the Sun. Thanks to your brilliance,
              we are able to take up the chase from Jesse's
              house! Please, click the link to the encrypted
              messenger below to read from Frank James’
              final entry in his journal.</p>



<p class="left">Sincerely,</p>
<p class="left">Q.</p>
